The paper deals with Visual Question Answering (VQA) tasks involving real images, which suggests that it belongs to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new model for reasoning over images, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses attention-based methods, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks, indicating that it may belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The paper also introduces a new network architecture, which involves progressive refinement, suggesting that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with multimodal data, specifically images and text, which suggests that it may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
